</div>
          </div>

            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-field-html-block field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__item"><p class="MsoBodyText">WASHINGTON (February 1, 2024)—Today, the U.S. Government Accountability Office (GAO) issued the 2024 revision of <em>Government Auditing Standards</em>, also known as the <a href="https://www.gao.gov/yellowbook">Yellow Book</a>. These standards, commonly referred to as generally accepted government auditing standards (GAGAS), provide a framework that auditors around the world use to perform high-quality audit work when reviewing government programs and spending. This revision provides updates to the 2018 version.</p></div>
      
  </div>

    </div>

</div>

  </div>

    </div>

  </div>


              </div>
                                  </div>
        </div>
      </main>
      </div> </div> 

